description:
After rescuing James from the clutches of an evil succubus, the fierce Lick Monsters of the Nether Regions find themselves pursued by a demonic horde intent on re-integrating their human captive into his proper (torturee) role in the Satanic hierarchy. Elisabeth, in her own spate of bad luck, finds herself lost in an increasingly dank and stuffy mall, where all the corridors seem to lead downward.

Creators Jennifer Feinberg and Todd Meister

2. I Called the Doctor

name: In the Company of Long Hair
The Best of Wimmen's Comix and Other Comix by Women

description:
THE FINAL ISSUE!

The big showdown between Alpha Flight and the Master of the World!
name: Pride of a Nation [Redux]

description: Collected from issues #30-36 and DOOM PATROL #19! A member of the team is determined to bring back a loved one from the Gates of Hell, and Bane must face his inner demons!
name: The Darkest House

first_appearance_objects.name: Get Out Of Hell Free Card

object_credits.name: Get Out Of Hell Free Card

description: The Kingpin of L.A. revealed in this standalone issue featuring Daken and FBI agent Donna Kiel. Can Daken be redeemed?
name: A Love Story?

description: The six-issue miniseries from Keith Giffen and Alex Horley is collected at last! Lobo's sunk as low as an intergalactic bounty hunter can sink – and now, he's vowed to climb back to the top of the heap by getting himself crowned the greatest mass murderer ever known!
name: TPB

description: Deadpool is about to be DEAD. Jump onboard readers, just as we kill our titular hero Deadpool!
name: Deadpool: The Musical

description: "LOST CHILDREN" Part Four Morley starts to understand the path laid before him as Green Wake begins to change after the rebellion settles, but the murders that happen behind the scenes are growing more mysterious. The heinous acts of violence hint at a growing thirst for blood.
name: Lost Children, Part 4

description:
Years have passed for the immortal samurai, now called Enma. He has embraced the demon within him and his new life as a tattoo artist, and has learned more secrets about his own master's former apprentice, who is also possessed by an immortal demon . . .

And, when the daughter of an old friend comes to Enma for help, the immortal has a chance to repay a life debt.
name: The Promise

volume.name: The Immortal: Demon in the Blood

description: First hailing Conan as a liberator after he annihilated Aquilonia's foes on the battlefield, common folk and politicians alike now rally to unseat the Cimmerian from his stolen throne. Conspirators plot to kill King Conan and take the crown for themselves, but their schemes pale in comparison to a terror waiting quietly in the wings--Thoth-Amon, an enemy who has haunted Conan his whole adult life and whose wicked aspirations dwarf those of maneuvering politicians!
name: The Phoenix on the Sword, Part 1: Daggers at my Back

volume.name: King Conan: The Phoenix on the Sword

description: The stakes are already high in a battle royale pitting Silver Star, Captain Victory and the Glory Knights versus Darius Drumm, the Lightning Lady and Roag over the Proto-Seed -- and when Sigurd Dragonsbane and the Mythics join in, the results will shake he heavens themselves. Meanwhile, Kirby's only hope for survival on the Phantom Continent lies in the Primals, whose secrets are rooted deep in the history of mankind itself.
name: From Out of the Depths

description: The unlikely couple of Nancy and Lucifer are back! After escaping from Hell, the chainsaw-wielding hottie finds that the Gates of Hades remained open, and all kind of demons are pouring out on Earth. Our world is the newest infernal region, and nobody will help the humans...not even the angels from Heaven!
name: Part 1 (of 4)

description: Captain America and Hawkeye undertake a mission to the Red Light Nation, a country run by criminals, for criminals!
name: Red Light Nation

description:
'Archie Meets KISS,' Part 3: 'Rock 'n Roll All Fright.' In part three of the most historic team-up in comics, the Archies learn more about what brought the KISS members to Riverdale, and how the two groups have to unite to stop a band of monsters from turning Riverdale into a forgotten town, full of zombified teens!

General Notes

Mr. Weatherbee, Moose Mason and Cheryl Blossom appear only on the cover.
name: Rock N' Roll All Fright!

description: Reprints political cartoons, Joe Bob Briggs and Ian Shoales columns, and comic strips: Calvin & Hobbes, The Far Side, Outland, Doonesbury, Angriest Dog in the World (David Lynch), and Life In Hell (Matt Groening)

Last year's groundbreaking Infestation series, IDW's first-ever event, saw many teams from multiple universes fight off a zombie invasion. Now, an even bigger threat has risen to threaten the growing IDW multiverse: Lovecraftian demons threaten to reach across time and space and destroy everyone everywhere and everywhen! Also featuring Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, this framing issue presents a threat that perhaps not even TRANSFORMERS, G.I. JOEs, Danger Girl, and others can surmount!

Volume 1, Number Five.

Published weekly by Jerome Sinkovec at Menomonee, Wisconsin, 53051.
name: Number Five

description:
In the first story, Spidey runs into some guys beating up on one guy. Spidey helps the guy, who was supposed to be pressed into an underground fighting tournament run by the Mandarin. When the Mandarin shows up, Spidey agrees to take the guy's place.

Spidey beats up a bunch of second- (and probably fifth-) rate guys, including Kangaroo and Constrictor over six rounds. In the last round he has to fight the Mandarin himself. He survives for a while but clearly can't beat the powerful Iron Man villain. So he uses his back-up plan, and calls in the Avengers, who settle things quickly.

In the second story, Blonde Phantom hires Spidey to catch Frog-Man. He catches Frog-Man quickly after he robs some jewelry. However the Black Cat shows up and steals both Frog-Man and the jewelry. Spidey chases after her, but her bad luck powers keep making him run into all kinds of unfortunate accidents.

When he finally catches up, she gives him a phone, over which the Blond Phantom tells him that she had also asked Felicia to catch Frog-Man. Black Cat just had him chase her for fun. She splits the reward with him.
name: Fight Club; Dumb Luck

description: Hawkeye's racing against time to clear the Avengers' names! In his last-ditch effort to save his friends, Hawkeye must team with the very man he's been charged with capturing! Meanwhile, the Avengers Academy vs. The West Coast Avengers.
name: Pathfinder - Part 4; The Sounds of Violence

description: Tanarus vs. Heimdall! Thor struggles to free himself before the Demogorge consumes him and a starship full of other fallen gods! What did Loki and the Surfer find in the desert and how can it help a god no one can remember?
name: The Mighty Tanarus: Part 3, Doomed

description: The rebellion grows! Yet disaster follows when the idealistic youth E'Tan and Gabrielle join the resistance...and come face-to-face with Royal Consort Lorelie and a network of druid spies. And shocking news arrives concerning the fate of King Icarus! Meanwhile, Pilot the Tall and Harad battle side-by-side against rat forces, and the training of One-Arm Leito takes a dark and tragic turn when the young hero embraces vengeance! The two-time Harvey Award-winning series continues, from the acclaimed writer of Thor: First Thunder and the co-creator of Powers and Takio!
name: Part 7: Snowblind

volume.name: The Mice Templar, Volume III: A Midwinter Night's Dream

description:
A mysterious illness is plaguing the streets of London and turning everyday humans into emotionless killers. The Watcher's Files, which may be the key to unraveling this mystery, have led Angel and Faith to seek out a demon from Giles's past for answers. Meanwhile a peculiar friend and foe returns to London and to Angel's inner circle.

* Executive producer Joss Whedon!

* A great jumping-on point!
name: Daddy Issues, Part 1

description: The twins are back, and they are after the King of Monsters himself! Riding into America on the backs of Battra and Rodan, the evil twins head toward Godzilla in an attempt to enslave the gargantuan to their will. But they may be underestimating the true power of Godzilla get ready for a battle of titans in Godzilla: Kingdom of Monsters #11!

Sideshow Bob returns to Springfield in the company of the rightful creator of Itchy and Scratchy, the hobo Chester J. Lampwick, but when the billionaire with a bindle goes missing, Bart suspects a certain sociopathic second banana. Meanwhile, Lisa makes it her mission to save the Springfield Library.
name: Sideshow Slob; Springfield General

description:
CELEBRATE THE FIFTEENTH ANNIVERSARY!

Fighting his way further into the Darkness dimension itself, Jackie Estacado will need be forced to decide what he is willing to sacrifice in order to confront and destroy the Darkness itself. Long time writer PHIL HESTER (Wonder Woman, Green Hornet) and ROMANO MOLENAAR (THE DARKNESS II: CONFESSION) barrel towards the landmark issue #100!
name: Total Darkness, Part Three: The Guts

volume.name: New Kids On The Block Comics Tour '90/91

description: THE ORIGIN OF THE SHIELD OF JUSTICE Back from the grave! The cult hit of 2011 returns with a tale of treachery, murder and unrequited lust. When headless corpses start to appear on the first night of the full moon, ace detective Johnny P. Sartre smells a rat Contains profanity, nudity, violence and the graphic depiction of alcohol abuse.
name: Killer Inside!

description:
Lost in the trackless, spider-infested depths of Hell, Elisabeth, Scrowlie, and company, must find the legendary "Brave One" if they ever expect to reach home. Led by a crack team of short, fat lick monsters, they set out on their journey, pursued by legions unknown. But even if they find their guide, the path out of Hell is not an easy one. In the land above, government forces, ever innovators, have discovered a financially-sound solution to the Fashion Zombies plaguing the nation's suburban shopping centers.

Creators Jennifer Feinberg and Todd Meister
Victor fights for his life aboard the alien mothership while Captain O'Toole and his squad take on the Formic death squads!

volume.name: Felix the Cat: House of 1,000 Ha! Ha’s!
Edgar Rice Burroughs Tarzan of the Apes

description: No gods from outer space could beat THIS Devil! Jack Kirby crossed into a new cosmos with this crimson carnivore and his faithful sidekick Moonboy! Now, for the first time, Marvel collects the King's saga of Devil Dinosaur in his prehistoric prime! Collecting DEVIL DINOSAUR #1-9.
name: HC/TPB

volume.name: Devil Dinosaur by Jack Kirby Omnibus
